<AbstractNarration>This is a 3-year Information Technology (IT) project, "DAMSALS," to provide 140 contact &lt;br/&gt;hours of professional development for 72 science, technology and mathematics teachers who in turn will provide 30 hours of staff supported IT instruction for 180 students.  The project&lt;br/&gt;uses the integrated science approach of past professional development efforts to deliver&lt;br/&gt;agriculture-related concepts.  Participants use GPS devices and graphing calculators with &lt;br/&gt;CBLs to collect data.  On-site visits, compressed video meetings and Blackboard &lt;br/&gt;discussions support implementation during the academic year.  Participants include students and teachers in grades 7-12 from rural schools in the Mississippi River Delta of northeast Louisiana.&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;</AbstractNarration>
